Did you know that the Women's Entrepreneurship Program is empowering women all over the world to start and grow their own businesses? This program provides access to training, mentorship, and resources that help women entrepreneurs succeed.

Research has shown that when women are empowered as entrepreneurs, it not only benefits them and their families, but it also strengthens their communities and contributes to the overall economic growth of their countries.

So if you or someone you know is a woman interested in starting or growing a business, be sure to check out the Women's Entrepreneurship Program. 💥Big News💥

I’m excited to share that I’m joining the local advisory council of @forbesblk_ , a global community of Black #entrepreneurs, professionals, #leaders, and creators who are driving systematic change in #business, #culture, and society.

 

The following opportunity will allow me to further amplify the current work I do in the Houston market Championing positive change and reducing racial disparities, in today's evolving landscape, empowering Black entrepreneurs, and non-profits is not just a goal—it's imperative. My commitment extends beyond words; it's reflected in my actions as I actively collaborate, invest, and advocate for equitable platforms and opportunities.

 

Feel free to connect with me as we build something special that will grant access to the Black community! #ForbesBLK www.forbes.com/forbesblk/

 

Plus, in case you missed it, we are headed to Atlanta on November 5-6 for the inaugural ForbesBLK Summit. This event will discuss the Future of Black entrepreneurialism and bring together culture, creativity, and community for one dynamic experience you will not forget. Register at the FobrbesBLK website .

"Discovering the beauty of the entrepreneurial journey is learning to love the process. 🚀💼

It's in the daily activities, the setbacks, and the small victories where we truly find our path to success. Like a gardener nurturing a seed, we water our ideas, cultivate our skills, and patiently watch them grow.

Entrepreneurship teaches us that success isn't just about reaching the destination; it's about cherishing each milestone, learning from every challenge, and celebrating the progress made. The process is our greatest teacher.

So, whether you're starting a new venture or forging ahead in your business, remember that the journey is where the magic happens. Embrace it, learn from it, and watch your dreams flourish. 🌟🌱 #EntrepreneurialJourney #LoveTheProcess #GrowthMindset"

A few months ago, we were given the incredible honor of being named as local leaders by @forbesblk_ . At that moment, we had no idea what this would entail or the profound impact it would have on our journey and the wider history of Black entrepreneurship. Fast forward to this past Monday, and we had the privilege of being part of ForbesBLK's first inaugural Summit, marking the kickoff to a series of initiatives designed to support and uplift Black #entrepreneurship.

During this Summit, we not only made history but also had the opportunity to connect with an amazing group of fellow entrepreneurs. The experience was a mix of knowledge-sharing, #networking, and some unforgettable moments of laughter. It reinforced the idea that our stories are not just about our personal accomplishments but are deeply intertwined with the people who surround us – our families and friends.

ForbesBLK has played a pivotal role in creating a remarkable and supportive community of entrepreneurs. It's a community that not only celebrates achievements but also helps us build our legacies. We are grateful to ForbesBLK for creating this sense of togetherness and empowerment. Our journey is just beginning, and we are excited to see what the future holds as we continue to build our legacies within this inspiring family. 🚀🙌 #ForbesBLK #Entrepreneurship #LegacyBuilders #CommunityMatters

Today was a deeply emotional day for me. Many of you know me from my PR work, but in a previous life, I was a Senior Compliance Analyst in the Oil and Gas industry. Back in 2019, I made the decision to step away from Oil and Gas to dedicate myself fully to my own business @innovating_marketing . 

During my time in Oil and Gas, I had the privilege to collaborate with the Federal Government and some truly remarkable colleagues. One person who made a profound impact on my career was the Senior Vice President of Ops. He took a chance on me, hiring me despite my lack of industry experience, but driven by determination. I joined as a contractor, poured my heart and soul into my work, and earned a seat at the table. Eventually, he offered me a full-time position and mentored me towards greatness. Together, we managed million-dollar budgets and spearheaded projects.

Today, my former boss uttered a simple phrase, 'I'm proud of you.' Those words meant the world to me. I visited my old workplace last year and realized I could easily return to Oil and Gas. But instead, I poured my heart and soul into building Innovating Marketing Group, creating outstanding campaigns for clients, and opening doors for women to seize opportunities. The path I've chosen is challenging, but it's also fulfilling. Here's to the journey ahead! 🌟💼 #CareerJourney #EmotionalDay #Entrepreneurship"
